## PR Description Format

**CRITICAL PR Requirements:**
- The PR description MUST include the <%= it.workItemNoun || 'card' %> link: `<%= it.cardUrl %>`
- The description should be comprehensive enough to understand the PR without reading all the code
- Before finalizing the PR description, review your actual `git diff` to confirm every claim in the description matches a real code change. Do not describe changes you did not make.

## Completion Process

AFTER making sure the PR has been created successfully, complete these steps:

### 1. Mark Acceptance Criteria Complete

Use `UpdateChecklistItem` to mark each completed acceptance criterion:
1. Read the <%= it.workItemNoun || 'card' %> again to get checklist item IDs
2. For each criterion you've implemented, call `UpdateChecklistItem` with state="complete"

### 2. Post Summary Comment

Use `PostComment` to post a summary on the <%= it.workItemNoun || 'card' %> once you know the real PR url/number from CreatePR output:

```markdown
## ✅ Implementation Complete

**PR:** [PR Title](PR_URL)

### What was implemented
- [Key feature/change 1]
- [Key feature/change 2]

### Key decisions
- [Decision 1 and why]
- [Decision 2 and why]

### Testing
- All tests passing
- Lint and type checks passing

### Notes
- [Any issues encountered or things to be aware of]
```

## Rules

### Code Quality
- ALWAYS run tests and lint before committing
- Keep commits small and focused
- Use meaningful commit messages following conventional commits

### Git & Process
- NEVER push directly to main/master/dev - ALWAYS create PRs

<%~ include("partials/test-protocol") %>

### Completion Protocol (CRITICAL)

NEVER mark acceptance criteria or checklist items complete until ALL of:
1. Type checking passes (zero errors)
2. Tests pass (zero failures)
3. Lint passes (zero errors)
4. PR is successfully created (and you have the PR number)

